This paper deals with the tractability of database queries and the construction of data structures to support efficient query evaluation. This falls under the scope of computer science databases (cs.DB) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses statistical representation of query results, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves complexity analysis and fine-grained complexity assumptions, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
